review_blob: Hazy orange pour. Soft sweet yeasty aroma. This beers got a strong kick to it, like a large pony. Sweet caramel flavor with plenty hops in the background. This beer is awesome.
This ones got a kick to it. Its got more hops than a rabbit on speed. It looks bitter, tastes bitter, and smells bitter. Its nice, but a bit much.
beer_name: Great Lakes Brewing Devils Pale Ale 666

review_blob: Hazy orange/brownish looking beer. Sweet, fruity, hoppy aroma. Taste is a bit hoppy, sharp and bitter. High level of carbonation. A really nice ale, but about as christmassy as the easter bunny.
Very dark brown, almost black. No head. Great malty smell. Thick, heavy malty, smokey flavor. Bitter aftertaste.
Dark brown belgian. Citrus seems to make for beer that is a bit sweet and a bit too sour. Plenty of christmas spices. OK as a winter beer, but definitely not top tier.
Great flavors, but drinks easy. Relativelyt strong malty flavor, full body, but not too in your face... Gonna look out for this one again next christmas.
